<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="173" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,823,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,823,848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Average forewing length: males 
<quantity box="[659,782,824,848]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14 mm</quantity>
(n = 6), females 
<quantity box="[987,1153,823,848]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.385" metricValueMax="1.45" metricValueMin="1.3199999999999998" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="13.85" valueMax="14.5" valueMin="13.2">13.2–14.5 mm</quantity>
(n = 3). This taxon was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[604,715,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Audre" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis box="[604,715,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its similarities and allopatric distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Callaghan" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Soares, A. (2001) A review of the Cinericiiformes section of the genus Audre Hemming and the description of a new subspecies (Riodinidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 18 (3), 755 - 763. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0101 - 81752001000300012" type="journal article" year="2001">Callaghan &amp; Soares 2001</bibRefCitation>
). However, more detailed evaluation of its morphology combined with the differences in the 
<collectionCode box="[1376,1437,896,920]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">DNA</collectionCode>
barcode (3.91%, 
<tableCitation box="[344,429,932,957]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,239,691,714]" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparison of inter- and intraspecific divergences (%) for the DNA “ barcodes ” of Sertania gen. nov. species (number of individuals in parentheses). Values of divergence above 2 percent are in bold; (--) does not apply." pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Table 2</tableCitation>
) indicate that the differences are more profound and that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[1085,1214,932,956]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis box="[1085,1214,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be raised to species status. The FW shape of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[518,721,968,992]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[518,721,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Sertania jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[727,970,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[727,970,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">comb. nov., stat nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1119,1300,968,992]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1119,1300,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Sertania guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1307,1436,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1307,1436,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in being relatively longer with a more pointed apex and the margin of both wing surfaces black instead of red; the male ventral HW post-medial area is nearly white in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[770,901,1040,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis box="[770,901,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1133,1243,1040,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis box="[1133,1243,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The frons of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dark brown with a small white spot in the middle; that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[961,1071,1076,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis box="[961,1071,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is white with two parallel light brown vertical lines. In the male genitalia, valvae are slightly longer with tips turned up in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1209,1318,1112,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis box="[1209,1318,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1337,1423,1111,1136]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[171,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Male genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 19 – 22, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Punta de los Llanos, La Rioja, Argentina (ZUEC), lateral view (19), tegumen and uncus in dorsal view (20), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (21), valvae in lateral view (22). 23 – 24, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. paratype from Diamantina, Minas Gerais, Brazil (DZUP), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (23), valvae in lateral view (24). 25 – 26, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (25), valvae in lateral view (26). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892883/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
), while they are shorter and truncated with straight tips in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[783,911,1148,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis box="[783,911,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[926,1010,1148,1173]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[171,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Male genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 19 – 22, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Punta de los Llanos, La Rioja, Argentina (ZUEC), lateral view (19), tegumen and uncus in dorsal view (20), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (21), valvae in lateral view (22). 23 – 24, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. paratype from Diamantina, Minas Gerais, Brazil (DZUP), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (23), valvae in lateral view (24). 25 – 26, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (25), valvae in lateral view (26). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892883/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); the pedicel is straight and pointed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[151,258,1184,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis box="[151,258,1184,1208]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and more curved and separated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[656,784,1184,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis box="[656,784,1184,1208]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the female genitalia, the ostium bursae is broader in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and more constricted caudad in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[601,729,1220,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis box="[601,729,1220,1244]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="173" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,823,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,502,1255,1280]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Biology and distribution.</emphasis>
The habitat of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[682,812,1256,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis box="[682,812,1256,1280]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transition between cerrado and caatinga vegetation. The 
<typeStatus box="[201,249,1293,1317]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">type</typeStatus>
locality between Jaíba and Mocambinho (
<quantity box="[721,795,1292,1316]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="490.0">490 m</quantity>
) in the 
<collectingRegion box="[879,1028,1292,1317]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
state presents a closed, tall-shrubby, xerophilous vegetation termed “Carrasco” with floristic elements of caatinga (
<bibRefCitation author="Callaghan" box="[1033,1329,1327,1352]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Soares, A. (2001) A review of the Cinericiiformes section of the genus Audre Hemming and the description of a new subspecies (Riodinidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 18 (3), 755 - 763. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0101 - 81752001000300012" type="journal article" year="2001">Callaghan &amp; Soares 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Besides the proximity of the São 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[435,756,1364,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="guttata" subSpecies="jaibensis">
Francisco River, 
<emphasis box="[627,756,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not inhabit gallery forests, which also form part of the habitat. The other two known localities in Diamantina and Sempre Vivas National Park consist of unique highaltitude (
<quantity box="[250,411,1436,1461]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="1200.0" valueMax="1500.0" valueMin="900.0">900 to 1500m</quantity>
) rocky outcrop vegetation (
<figureCitation box="[724,806,1436,1461]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 37" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1200,1222]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1179]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,193,1179]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 37. Overview of Sertania gen. nov. habitats in South American ‘ dry diagonal’. 34 – 35, Sertania guttata comb. nov., monte vegetation (34) in Anillaco, La Rioja, and Chaco serrano (35) in Capilla del Monte, Cordoba, Argentina; 36, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov., rocky montane fields in Sempre Vivas National Park, Buenópolis, Minas Gerais, Brazil; 37, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov., arboreal caatinga in Custódia, Pernambuco, Brazil. Photos (36) by CA Iserhard and (37) by DHA Melo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892889/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) locally known as “campos rupestres” typical of higher parts of the “Serra do Espinhaço” range (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Alves" box="[680,941,1471,1496]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" refString="Alves, R. J. V. &amp; Kolbek, J. (2010) Can campo rupestre vegetation be floristically delimited based on vascular plant genera? Plant Ecology, 207, 67 - 79. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11258 - 009 - 9654 - 8" type="journal article" year="2010">Alves &amp; Kolbek 2010</bibRefCitation>
). This species is absent from the Brazilian central Plateau to the south of this locality. Butterflies fly rapidly and close to the ground at mid-day, resting with open wings on leaf dorsal surfaces, in apparent contrast to the more sedentary behavior of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1159,1266,1544,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis box="[1159,1266,1544,1568]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As mentioned above, the species is known from only three localities in northern 
<collectingRegion box="[890,1044,1580,1605]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
